# ShareWind Android — Project Overview

## Architecture
Clean Architecture + MVVM. Three layers, strict dependency direction:
```
ui/ → domain/ → data/
```
- `ui/` — Jetpack Compose screens + ViewModels
- `domain/` — pure Kotlin use cases, models, repository interfaces
- `data/` — Retrofit, DataStore, repository implementations

## Dependency Injection
All dependencies injected via **Hilt**. No manual singletons except Hilt-managed `@Singleton` bindings.

## Two App Modes (same APK)
- **End-user mode** — browse driver rides, create requests, accept offers
- **Driver mode** — browse EU requests, create rides, send offers, manage vehicles
- Role is stored in DataStore; users with dual-role can toggle in-session

## Critical Business Rules
- Driver accounts start `pending` — UI must show a "waiting for approval" state
- Offers expire in **10 minutes** — countdown must be shown in the offer UI
- Phone numbers are only revealed **after confirmation** — never display before `confirmed` status
- Free plan: EU 120 requests/month, Driver 30 rides/month — show quota in profile
- FCM token must be re-registered on every login and on `onNewToken`

## Tech Stack
Kotlin · Jetpack Compose · Hilt · Retrofit + OkHttp · Coroutines + Flow · DataStore · FCM · Coil · Material 3
